<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-04T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-04T23:00:00-05:00" n="710" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">125.288M/1–548: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-05T12:00:00+08:00">January 5,
                                1948—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 5—5:53 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>16. We consider that closing office at Changchun would have adverse effect on
                        public morale, thus further weakening Government position Changchun-Kirin
                        area. (ReDeptel 1586, December 31.) Siebens<note n="3" xml:id="d710fn3">Allen C. Siebens, Vice Consul at Changchun.</note> has expressed to
                        Embassy his desire to remain Changchun even in the event it falls to
                        Communists. We feel that he should be allowed to remain and in the event the
                        city falls we would thereby have some indication of what the Communist
                        attitude would be toward American Consular offices in other areas of
                        China.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>